// Render UI Tool
// Broadcasts a JSON UI definition to connected browser clients via WebSocket
// and optionally blocks until the user takes an action in the browser.

In blocking mode (the default), the call does not timeout — it waits indefinitely
until handleUIResponse is called with a matching componentId.
Pending handlers are stored on the wsHandler instance under __pendingUIHandlers[uiId].

FUNCTION validateUIStructure(ui) -> asserts UIComponent                          EXPORT
  Validate that ui is a non-null object with a string type and an object props.
  If children is present, validate it is an array and recursively validate each child.
  If actions is present, validate it is an array where each action has string id and label.
  Throw descriptive errors on any validation failure.

---

FUNCTION renderUI(project, session, ui, blocking?, wsHandler) -> RenderUIResponse  EXPORT
  Validate project and session are non-empty strings.
  Validate ui structure via validateUIStructure.
  Generate a unique uiId, then broadcast a ui_render message to all browser clients.
  IF blocking is false, return immediately with { completed: true, source: 'terminal', action: 'render_complete' }.
  IF blocking is true, return a Promise that resolves only when handleUIResponse is called
  with the matching uiId. Register the resolve callback under wsHandler.__pendingUIHandlers[uiId].

---

FUNCTION handleUIResponse(wsHandler) -> void                                     EXPORT
  Lookup the pending handler for response.componentId in wsHandler.__pendingUIHandlers.
  IF found, call the handler with the response and remove it from the map.

---

FUNCTION createUIResponse(uiId, actionId, data?) -> UIResponse                   EXPORT
  Build and return a UIResponse object for testing purposes.
